President Obama has proclaimed March 22, 2013, as Education and Sharing Day, U.S.A. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of education and passing on values to future generations. He states that education is essential for our children to succeed in the 21st-century economy and calls on parents, teachers, and mentors to instill important virtues in children. The day also commemorates the work of Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson, who promoted education and good character. President Obama urges all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.